==English==
===Etymology===
Generic of the former U.S. trademark ''Granola'', from the then U.S. trademark ''Granula''

===Noun===
{{Wikipedia}}
'''granola'''

# A [[breakfast]] and [[snack]] food consisting of loose, crispy pellets made of nuts, rolled oats, honey and other natural ingredients.

====Usage notes====
In Australia, '''Granola''' is maintained as a trademark by Sanitarium Health Food Company.

